{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01P9Vzotun3AfGEbV9sratf5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016z3yMxPR2WwAu4VkD717sf","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Read Methodology sheet structure","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"Read the Methodology sheet from the Excel workbook at C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx\n\nWrite a Node.js script to read this sheet and output:\n1. The value of cell A1 (template instructions)\n2. All non-empty cells with their addresses and values\n3. The sheet dimensions\n\nRun the script and return the full output.\n\nUse this script:\n```javascript\nconst XLSX = require('xlsx');\nconst path = require('path');\n\nconst filePath = 'C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx';\nconst wb = XLSX.readFile(filePath);\n\nconst sheetName = wb.SheetNames.find(n => n.toLowerCase().includes('method'));\nconsole.log('Sheet name:', sheetName);\n\nconst ws = wb.Sheets[sheetName];\nconst range = ws['!ref'];\nconsole.log('Range:', range);\n\n// Print all non-empty cells\nconst decoded = XLSX.utils.decode_range(range);\nfor (let r = decoded.s.r; r <= decoded.e.r; r++) {\n  for (let c = decoded.s.c; c <= decoded.e.c; c++) {\n    const addr = XLSX.utils.encode_cell({r, c});\n    const cell = ws[addr];\n    if (cell && cell.v !== undefined && cell.v !== '') {\n      console.log(`${addr}: ${JSON.stringify(cell.v)}`);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSave it to C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/read_methodology.js, run it with node, and return the full output."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2066,"cache_read_input_tokens":14418,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2066,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4a5998dc-503b-4df4-b16c-7a512e7e5d41","uuid":"a1b94736-b087-4516-ba10-631f1564aff2"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_started","task_id":"afd37e0f8a645629f","tool_use_id":"toolu_016z3yMxPR2WwAu4VkD717sf","description":"Read Methodology sheet structure","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"Read the Methodology sheet from the Excel workbook at C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx\n\nWrite a Node.js script to read this sheet and output:\n1. The value of cell A1 (template instructions)\n2. All non-empty cells with their addresses and values\n3. The sheet dimensions\n\nRun the script and return the full output.\n\nUse this script:\n```javascript\nconst XLSX = require('xlsx');\nconst path = require('path');\n\nconst filePath = 'C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx';\nconst wb = XLSX.readFile(filePath);\n\nconst sheetName = wb.SheetNames.find(n => n.toLowerCase().includes('method'));\nconsole.log('Sheet name:', sheetName);\n\nconst ws = wb.Sheets[sheetName];\nconst range = ws['!ref'];\nconsole.log('Range:', range);\n\n// Print all non-empty cells\nconst decoded = XLSX.utils.decode_range(range);\nfor (let r = decoded.s.r; r <= decoded.e.r; r++) {\n  for (let c = decoded.s.c; c <= decoded.e.c; c++) {\n    const addr = XLSX.utils.encode_cell({r, c});\n    const cell = ws[addr];\n    if (cell && cell.v !== undefined && cell.v !== '') {\n      console.log(`${addr}: ${JSON.stringify(cell.v)}`);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSave it to C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/read_methodology.js, run it with node, and return the full output.","uuid":"37028c7e-b290-4f4e-be37-64a913f1dbaf","session_id":"4a5998dc-503b-4df4-b16c-7a512e7e5d41"}
