decision rules applied per vendor based on strategic value, spend level, and category overlap\"\nA15: \"Opportunity prioritisation: top 3 opportunities selected using multi-factor evaluation across financial impact, execution effort, business risk, and time to value\"\nA16: \"\" (empty)\nA17: \"PROMPTS:\"\nA18: \"A 16-step structured prompt workflow was designed and executed sequentially via Claude Code CLI\"\nA19: \"Each step had a single clearly scoped analytical task: inspect, classify, score, identify, validate, or document\"\nA20: \"Key prompts covered: workbook inspection, vendor classification, duplicate detection, strategic scoring, opportunity identification, methodology documentation, and executive memo generation\"\nA21: \"All prompts enforced strict output format rules: allowed departments, recommendation values, cell-level write constraints, and sheet-level write guards\"\nA22: \"Prompts were passed to Claude Code CLI via stdin pipe in non-interactive mode using printf\"\nA23: \"\" (empty)\nA24: \"TOOLS:\"\nA25: \"Claude Code CLI (Anthropic): AI reasoning and analytical tasks across all 16 steps\"\nA26: \"Node.js with xlsx (SheetJS) library: Excel workbook read and write operations throughout the pipeline\"\nA27: \"Python with openpyxl: post-pipeline formatting restoration from the original template\"\nA28: \"Bash orchestration script: step sequencing, checkpoint and resume logic, and log capture across all pipeline stages\"\n\nSave the script to C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/write_methodology.js, run it, verify A1 is unchanged, and confirm all 4 sections were written successfully.\n\nScript template:\n```javascript\nconst XLSX = require('xlsx');\n\nconst filePath = 'C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx';\nconst wb = XLSX.readFile(filePath);\n\nconst sheetName = wb.SheetNames.find(n => n.toLowerCase().includes('method'));\nconst ws = wb.Sheets[sheetName];\n\n// Verify A1 is preserved\nconsole.log('A1 (must not change):', ws['A1'] ? ws['A1'].v : '(empty)');\n\n// Helper to set a cell value\nfunction setCell(addr, value) {\n  const cell = ws[addr];\n  if (cell) {\n    cell.v = value;\n    cell.w = value;  // formatted text\n    if (cell.t === undefined) cell.t = 's';\n  } else {\n    ws[addr] = { v: value, t: 's' };\n  }\n}\n\n// Write all content cells (skip A1)\n// ... write each cell using setCell\n\n// Update sheet range if needed\n// ws['!ref'] = 'A1:A28';\n\nXLSX.writeFile(wb, filePath);\nconsole.log('Done. Verifying...');\n\n// Re-read and verify\nconst wb2 = XLSX.readFile(filePath);\nconst ws2 = wb2.Sheets[sheetName];\nconsole.log('A1:', ws2['A1'] ? ws2['A1'].v : '(empty)');\nconsole.log('A3:', ws2['A3'] ? ws2['A3'].v : '(empty)');\nconsole.log('A9:', ws2['A9'] ? ws2['A9'].v : '(empty)');\nconsole.log('A17:', ws2['A17'] ? ws2['A17'].v : '(empty)');\nconsole.log('A24:', ws2['A24'] ? ws2['A24'].v : '(empty)');\nconsole.log('A28:', ws2['A28'] ? ws2['A28'].v : '(empty)');\n```\n\nComplete the script with all the cell writes and run it. Return the full output including verification.","uuid":"61fc88aa-e1f0-4830-9dbb-5a78b5c679a0","session_id":"4a5998dc-503b-4df4-b16c-7a512e7e5d41"}
